# SDG-WAYSHELL Tips

1. Volume OSD appears when moving cursor to the right edge of any monitor
2. Brightness OSD appears when moving cursor to the left edge of any monitor
3. Screenshot toolbar appears at the top-center of any monitor
4. Monocle bars show window switchers per monitor when in monocle/deck layouts
5. Elevated (root/sudo) processes are listed in the bottom-left zone
6. Focused process CPU, RAM, and GPU usage in the bottom-right zone
7. Layout-switching bars change automatically — no manual toggle needed
8. Config hot-reload: `pkill wayshell && wayshell &` picks up changes to wayshell.conf and wayshell.modules
9. Matugen Material You colors apply to all bars dynamically via colors.css import
10. Cursor zone sensitivity is controlled by zone_buffer in wayshell.conf (default: 30px from edge)
